HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 331
By Terry
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Middle Tennessee
State University Blue Raiders club hockey team,
Ameritrans Cup and College Hockey South
Conference champions.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful collegiate teams that, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor
to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, the Middle Tennessee State University (MTSU) Blue Raiders club hockey
team achieved an extraordinary level of success during the 2024-2025 season, winning their
first ever Ameritrans Cup, which is awarded to the champions of the College Hockey South
Conference; and
WHEREAS, the MTSU Blue Raiders hoisted their first ever Ameritrans Cup by defeating
the University of South Florida (USF) Bulls by a score of 4-0 to clinch the program's first College
Hockey Conference championship on February 23, 2025; and
WHEREAS, on their path to their first ever conference championship, the Blue Raiders
defeated Tampa 6-2 and Ole Miss 4-1 before their ultimate victory over USF to secure the right
to hoist the Ameritrans Cup; and
WHEREAS, the 2024-2025 MTSU Blue Raiders enjoyed the services of an outstanding
coaching staff led by Head Coach JJ Murray, who instilled in these exceptional young men a
commitment to excellence in all they do and encouraged maximum effort on the ice; and
WHEREAS, conference championships are won through hard work, dedication, and a
commitment to working together as a team and excelling with a cooperative spirit; the Blue
Raiders exhibited each of these rare qualities during their championship season; and
